      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "(** * Definition of a functor *)",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Import Category.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Set Implicit Arguments.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Generalizable All Variables.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Declare Scope functor_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Delimit Scope functor_scope with functor.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope morphism_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Section Functor.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Variables C D : PreCategory.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  (** Quoting from the lecture notes for MIT's 18.705, Commutative Algebra:\n\n      A map of categories is known as a functor. Namely, given\n      categories [C] and [C'], a (covariant) functor [F : C -> C'] is\n      a rule that assigns to each object [A] of [C] an object [F A] of\n      [C'] and to each map [m : A -> B] of [C] a map [F m : F A -> F\n      B] of [C'] preserving composition and identity; that is,\n\n     (1) [F (m' \u2218 m) = (F m') \u2218 (F m)] for maps [m : A -> B] and [m' :\n         B -> C] of [C], and\n\n     (2) [F (id A) = id (F A)] for any object [A] of [C], where [id A]\n         is the identity morphism of [A]. **)\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Record Functor :=\n    {\n      object_of :> C -> D;\n      morphism_of : forall s d, morphism C s d\n                                -> morphism D (object_of s) (object_of d);\n      composition_of : forall s d d'\n                              (m1 : morphism C s d) (m2: morphism C d d'),\n                         morphism_of _ _ (m2 o m1)\n                         = (morphism_of _ _ m2) o (morphism_of _ _ m1);\n      identity_of : forall x, morphism_of _ _ (identity x)\n                              = identity (object_of x)\n    }.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "End Functor.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Bind Scope functor_scope with Functor.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Create HintDb functor discriminated.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Arguments Functor C D : assert.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Arguments object_of {C%_category D%_category} F%_functor c%_object : rename, simpl nomatch.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Arguments morphism_of [C%_category] [D%_category] F%_functor [s%_object d%_object] m%_morphism : rename, simpl nomatch.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Arguments composition_of [C D] F _ _ _ _ _ : rename.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Arguments identity_of [C D] F _ : rename.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Module Export FunctorCoreNotations.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  (** Perhaps we should consider making this more global? *)\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Notation \"C --> D\" := (Functor C D) : type_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Notation \"F '_0' x\" := (object_of F x) : object_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Notation \"F '_1' m\" := (morphism_of F m) : morphism_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "End FunctorCoreNotations.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "#[export]\nHint Resolve composition_of identity_of : category functor.",
      "messages": [],
